{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So in Westerbork-- he was in Westerbork saying he was British, but he couldn't prove it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he had to go via this chain, the Swiss embassy and the Hague, to Switzerland and then to Britain, to get a copy of his passport or his birth certificate.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Did you meet him in Westerbork?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, he was there before us, [? long ?] before us-- early in '42.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I've met him since and I've heard his story.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In our case, we were kept in Westerbork for a very long time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I've told you now the bad part about Westerbork, which is the deportations every Tuesday morning of around about 1,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, for us, we just stayed in Westerbork all the time because, as we found out, we had the blue stamp, and they hadn't decided yet what they were going to do with us.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When we got to Westerbork, two grandparents had already been deported.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other grandparents, the paternal grandparents, were still in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But within a couple of weeks of us arriving there-- I mean, we saw them every day because Westerbork, basically, was quite a good camp, really, where you could meet people and all those sort of things.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we met them every day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We saw them every day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But very soon after we arrived, one night they were on the list kind of thing",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And every evening, Monday evening, in each barrack, the names of the people who had to be transported were read out of those who were in that barrack.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Only those in that barrack were read out.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
